bush flax
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:<i>Astelia nervosa</i>  (prob. from `growing in the bush A1, rather than from gen. Eng. `growing as a bush; bush-sized'); a tussocky, flax-like plant (astelia) with berries, red when ripe, found usually in bush; also called kakaha.


